hint /hɪnt/

(hinting,hinted,hints) 

1. N-COUNT A hint is a suggestion about something that is made in an indirect way. 暗示 

例： I'd dropped a hint about having an exhibition of his work up here. 我暗示要在这里举办一次他的作品展。 

2. PHRASE If you take a hint , you understand something that is suggested to you indirectly. 领会暗示 

例： 'I think I hear the telephone ringing.'—'Okay, I can take a hint.' “我想我听见了电话在响。”—“好的，我明白你的意思。” 

3. V-I If you hint at something, you suggest it in an indirect way. 暗示 

例： She hinted at the possibility of a treat of some sort. 她暗示可以找找乐子什么的。 

4. N-COUNT A hint is a helpful piece of advice, usually about how to do something. 建议 

例： Here are some helpful hints to make your journey easier. 这里是一些有用的建议，可以使你的旅途更舒适。 

5. N-SING A hint of something is a very small amount of it. 微量 

例： She added only a hint of vermouth to the gin. 她往杜松子酒里只加了一点儿苦艾酒。

